Build a credit risk prediction model and apply SHAP and LIME to explain global and local decisions. Compare both methods, analyze discrepancies, and produce an interpretable, regulator-friendly explanation framework for fair and transparent loan approvals.

This project implements an Entropy-Guided Hybrid Stacking Ensemble (E-HSE) framework for accurate and explainable Polycystic Ovary Syndrome (PCOS) detection. The model combines advanced machine learning techniques with dual explainability mechanisms to provide clinically interpretable predictions.

In this project, we developed a forecasting framework that outperforms Ternas baseline predictions by integrating statistical and machine learning models within a rolling forecasting pipeline, using ensemble averaging and systematic evaluation across multiple Italian regions

Portfolio Optimization is a data science project that creates investment portfolios to maximize returns and manage risk using mean-variance optimization and machine learning. It features customizable workflows and frameworks like PyPortfolioOpt, designed for finance students and early-career data scientists.

Machine learning models for optimizing beneficiary targeting in Peru's Pension 65 social program. Case study: Arapa district, Azngaro province, Puno region. Pax is a Jax-based machine learning framework for training large scale models. Pax allows for advanced and fully configurable experimentation and parallelization, and has demonstrated industry leading model flop utilization rates.

This project implements a Supervised Machine Learning (ML) framework to accurately predict the cost of an Electric Vehicle (EV) based on its key features and specifications. This is fundamentally a regression problem, aiming to determine a continuous value (price) from a set of input variables (features).

Implemented an efficient multilabel learning framework using Machine Learning Group Testing (MLGT). Designed code matrices via random construction and ReedSolomonbased methods, evaluated Precision@k vs. Hamming Loss, and optimized the training and prediction pipeline to achieve a 70% reduction in execution time compared to the One-vs-All model.

This project develops neural-network surrogate models for fast, accurate European option pricing under stochastic volatility frameworks.
